                        "content": "The nurse teaches the spouse of a client who is receiving levodopa/carbidopa to avoid pyridoxine medications. Which statement by the wife indicates an understanding of the instructions?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nPyridoxine (vitamin B6) reverses the therapeutic effects of levodopa. Dietary restrictions are unnecessary, but the ingredients in multivitamins need to be assessed. Many multivitamins contain pyridoxine and need to be avoided. Careful reading of over-the-counter vitamin labeling is necessary to avoid increasing pyridoxine in the diet. The statements in the remaining options are incorrect.",
