                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nWith carbidopa/levodopa therapy, a darkening of the urine or sweat may occur. The client would be reassured that this is a harmless effect of the medication, and its use should be continued. Darkened urine is not indicative of carbidopa/levodopa toxicity, the result of taking the medication with milk, or a sign of interaction with another medication.",
